comments.body:
@ashb this is embarrassing, but I just realized that I messed this up when I made the change for code review. It actually works as is (which is why I didn't catch it!), but only because I was "lucky" -- `val` is already defined in the global scope, from what I can tell.

I would like to change this script to:
```
    const val = document.getElementById('val');
    const height = Math.min(window.innerHeight * 0.5, val.scrollHeight);
    val.style.height = `${height}px`;
```
What's the best course of action here? Do I need to create a Jira ticket for this?

